node.text: The living legend @MikeHornExplorer tells us about the horrible scenes he has witnessed during his adventures and the importance of the young generations in the race to save our planet ! We must all get together now and start moving, it’s time for action ! Our special thanks to @spgrytz for supporting our vision towards a sustainable environment! #DiscoverEarth

node.text:
Stunning photos of Montana’s nature 🍃 Which is your favourite?

Montana is filled with natural beauty. The state is also home to the Glacier National Park that boasts over 700 miles of trails, dotted with lakes, mountains and alpine meadows, so it might just be the perfect next adventure for hikers. ⛰️🇺🇸

Insider tip: As the park is quite big with so much to see, plan to stay at least 2-3 days to have enough time to enjoy its beauty.

📍Montana, United States

🇺🇸 #discoverUnited States with @kurtisminster

node.text:
If you encounter a bear:⁣⁣
- Stay calm. If the bear sees you, talk in a low, calm voice and then regardless if it has seen you or not.⁣⁣
- Back up slowly. Never turn your back on a bear, or run. Running could trigger an attack.⁣⁣
- Do not stare. The bear will see a direct stare as a challenge.⁣⁣
- Give it space. Make sure it has a way to get away, and that you are not blocking access to a bear’s cubs or its food.⁣⁣

📍Alaska, United States

🇺🇸 #discoverUnitedStates
Video by @carasiciliano

Uncovering one of the 7 New Wonders of the World with @visualsofjulius 🤯

Located in Jordan, Petra (also known as “Rose City), is a famous archaeological site with a heritage that goes all the way back to 300 B.C.. Petra’s pink and red sandstone cliffs are home to stunning, ornate tombs and temples, making it an unforgettable site for tourists. Would you visit Petra?

📍Jordan

🇯🇴 #discoverJordan with @visualsofjulius

A secluded, coastal sanctuary 🌊 Would you live in this house?

Nestled within the rocks, Castle Meur is not your average home. This cottage was built in 1861 in the tranquil village of Plougrescant, France, and has become one of the most charming tourist attractions of the area. 

📍Plougrescant, France

Rugged (yet absolutely beautiful!) little fellow 🦜😍

You can find the Kea parrot in the alpine regions of New Zealand’s South Island. Kea parrots are known to be very smart and mischievous, and incredibly rare. Have you seen a parrot like this before?

📍New Zealand

🇳🇿 #discoverNewZealand with @long.explorer

node.text:
Quiet mornings in the best company 🦌✨ Would you join these white deer for a walk in the forest?

While some deer are now extinct in Bangladesh and Pakistan, you can still come across them in regions of central and Northern India, and in Nepal. They’re also called the Barasingha (meaning twelve ends), which refers to the many-tined antlers of these majestic deer.

📍Himachal Pradesh, india

🇮🇳#discoverIndia via @discoverwildlife
